# UI design — Verytel (minimalist, white)

**Direction:** structure & density like Pipedrive (work tool, tables/pipeline first);
the analytic visual language (donut, heatmap, area charts, gradient banner) is reserved
for **Dashboards/Analytics (Wave 2)** only. Default screen = white, calm, content-first.

**Tokens — use variables, never hardcode** (`frontend/src/styles/tokens.css`):
- `--brand-primary #0033A0` → active sidebar item, header, primary buttons.
- `--brand-turquoise #2DCCD3` → ACCENT ONLY: positive indicators, a single active icon.
  Never as a large fill or background.
- `--ink #1D1D1B` → primary text / high contrast.
- Chart-only blues: `--navy #0E1B5C`, `--blue-500 #1E4FD8`, `--sky #8FB8FF`. Charts/states only,
  never navigation.
- Surfaces: `--bg #F5F6FA` (app canvas), `--surface #FFFFFF` (cards). White dominates.

**Type:** family = `"Century Gothic", "Questrial", system-ui, sans-serif`. Century Gothic is
not yet licensed as a webfont → Questrial (geometric, Google Fonts) is the working fallback.
Max 2 type roles per section. `Aller` only in the logo SVG, never in UI.

**Components:** prefer building from tokens (radius `--radius 10px`, spacing scale 4/8/12/16/24).
Buttons: primary = brand-primary solid; secondary = ghost with ink text. Tables: zebra off,
hairline row dividers, generous row height. Keep one bold element per screen; remove the rest.

**Copy:** sentence case, active voice, plain verbs. Errors explain what to do, no apologies.
Empty states invite an action. Spanish UI copy; same domain terms as code.
